    summary:
      "2010 was a year of recovery. Book value rose 13.0%, compounding at 20.1% annually over 46 years. Berkshire's net worth increased by $21.6 billion. Significant bolt-on acquisitions across operating businesses. Insurance float reached $65.8 billion. BNSF Railway and MidAmerican Energy delivered record earnings. Capital expenditures were $6.5 billion. The housing market showed early signs of stabilization. Berkshire's diversified model proved resilient in the post-crisis environment.",
