<p>1990 ................... 7,798 1980-1990 26.3%</p>
<p>2000 ................... 50,229 1990-2000 20.5%</p>
<p>2010 ................... 94,730 2000-2010 6.6%</p>
<p>Though our compounded annual increase in per-share investments was a healthy 19.9% over the</p>
<p>40-year period, our rate of increase has slowed sharply as we have focused on using funds to buy operating</p>
<p>businesses.</p>
<p>The payoff from this shift is shown in the following table, which illustrates how earnings of our</p>
<p>non-insurancebusinesseshaveincreased,againonaper-sharebasisandafterapplicableminorityinterests.</p>
