<p>Letmequantify Tony’sachievement. When,in1996,weboughtthe50%of GEICOwedidn’talready</p>
<p>own,itcostusabout$2.3billion. Thatpriceimpliedavalueof$4.6billionfor100%. GEICOthenhadtangible</p>
<p>networthof$1.9billion.</p>
<p>The excess over tangible net worth of the implied value – $2.7 billion – was what we estimated</p>
