<p>company’s Vice Chairman, and I will not change yardsticks. It’s our job to increase intrinsic business</p>
<p>value–forwhichweusebookvalueasasignificantlyunderstatedproxy–atafasterratethanthemarket</p>
<p>gains of the S&P. If wedoso, Berkshire’s share price, though unpredictable from year toyear,willitself</p>
<p>outpacethe S&Povertime. Ifwefail,however,ourmanagementwillbringnovaluetoourinvestors,who</p>
<p>themselvescanearn S&Preturnsbybuyingalow-costindexfund.</p>
<p>Charlieand Ibelievethegainin Berkshire’sintrinsicvaluewillovertimelikelysurpassthe S&Preturnsby</p>
<p>a small margin. We’re confident of that because we have some outstanding businesses, a cadre of terrific</p>
